Casting call!!! Jobbet er dsv UL√òNNET

Her p√• Talentskolen I N√¶stved  er vi lige g√•et i gang med vores f√∏rste √∏velse for i √•r hvor vi skal filme og producere en meget lille kortfilm p√• ca 2 min og har derfor brug for en nogle dejlige skuespillere.

Det er en dags optagelse her n√¶ste m√•ned (s√∏ndag d. 1 Nov.)

Filmning vil foreg√• i N√¶stved, og transport og forplejning st√•r vi for, s√• ikke v√¶re bange for at skrive.

Der vil v√¶re √∏velser nogle uger f√∏r filming s√• man ikke bare m√∏der op og f√•r et manus i h√•nden. 

**Vi s√∏ger 3 skuespiller 2 m√¶nd og 1 dame **

m√¶ndene m√• godt v√¶re i spille alderen (26-35)

og en kvindelig skuespiller i spille alderen (50+)

Hvis i er interesseret skal i bare skrive til mig privat p√• facebook s√• svar jeg s√• hurtigt som muligt 
og hvis i kender nogle der m√•ske kunne v√¶re interesseret s√• skal i bare tagge dem i kommentaren

**Logline:**
To venner forbereder sig p√• en vigtig aften, men bliver gentagne gange forstyrret af hverdagens sm√• trivialiteter, cigaretter, lasagne og en mor, der bare vil v√¶re hj√¶lpsom.

**Filmes genre:** Sort komedie

* **William (28 ish)**

William er en kontrollerende og lettere ansp√¶ndt type, der fors√∏ger at tage ansvar og holde styr p√• situationen ‚Äì uanset hvor kaotisk eller banal den er. Han er tydeligt frustreret over sin mors konstante afbrydelser og Theodors manglende fokus. Under overfladen ligger et behov for at bevise sig selv ‚Äì m√•ske over for verden, m√•ske over for sig selv.

* **Theoder (28 ish)**

Theodor er afslappet og lidt fjern, en dr√∏mmer med et t√∏rt glimt i √∏jet. Han tager ikke situationen n√¶r s√• seri√∏st som William og reagerer p√• kaos med humor eller passivitet. Han er loyal, men lidt af en wildcard ‚Äì det er aldrig helt til at sige, om han er genial eller bare helt v√¶k. Hans m√•de at "leve sig ind i rollen" viser b√•de legesyge og en snert af noget m√∏rkere.

* **Williams mor**

En klassisk overbeskyttende og p√•tr√¶ngende mor, der tydeligvis ikke forst√•r gr√¶nser ‚Äì men heller ikke mener noget ondt med det. Hun tr√¶der ind i scenen med lasagne og str√∏mpebukser og underminerer al "alvor" med hver s√¶tning. Hendes komiske timing og totale mangel p√• situations fornemmelse fungerer som en ufrivillig sabot√∏r af s√∏nnens hemmelige planer.

H√•ber at h√∏re fra jer snart 

Mvh.
Andrim, Lisa, Alexander, Lukas og Lukas

** ùêéùêçùêãùêò ùüí ùêñùêÑùêÑùêäùêí ùêìùêé ùêÜùêé **

 

Tickets are now available for our upcoming Actors and Filmmakers Networking Event, taking place on Sunday, October 26th.

 

Networking is essential for advancing your career in the industry, and Marble Academy has proudly facilitated these events for years. With over 90 attendees, our June gathering was a tremendous success, and we are determined to build on that momentum.

 

You will have the opportunity to connect with accomplished actors, visionary directors, prominent producers, and skilled crew members who can offer valuable insights and spark meaningful collaborations.

 

Think about it, if there were an event where you could connect with exceptionally talented cast and crew who could help bring your next project to life, wouldn‚Äôt you want to be there?

 

So, join us on Sunday, October 26th, from 2 PM to 6:30 PM at HOME Mcr, located at 2 Tony Wilson Place, Manchester, M15 4FN.

 

Secure your tickets through this link:

https://www.eventbrite.co.uk/e/actors-and-filmmakers-networking-event-tickets-1509159349239 

 

I look forward to seeing you there!

Our last Self-Tape Workshop filled up quickly, leaving many interested individuals unable to attend, but don‚Äôt worry, we're excited to announce that another chance is just around the corner!

 

Join us at Marble Academy in Swinton, Manchester, on Monday, December 1st

 

You'll acquire practical insights and techniques that'll enhance your performance in auditions, boost your confidence on camera and create standout self-tapes!

 

**Spaces are VERY Limited!**

Here, you won‚Äôt just learn; you‚Äôll train with one of the best in the business!

His insightful feedback doesn‚Äôt just boost your confidence; it ignites your growth as an actor, providing you with a fresh perspective on every script. With his nurturing and constructive coaching style, you‚Äôll be amazed at how he can transform your journey as an actor.

items.text: I am trying to find any information about Duncan Cawthra born in June 1938 who was an actor and ASM at Lincoln Rep in 1962. In 1980 he was on the ‚Äúno longer a member of Equity‚Äù list. From 1969 to 1977 he is occasionally listed as Costume Designer for some tv programmes, and the trail ends in1981 as Wardrobe Supervisor for a film called ‚ÄúThe Mouse and the Woman‚Äù. From 2003 to 2010 he lived in a nursing home in Plymouth where he died. He was supposed to be best man at my wedding in 1963 but never turned up and I have often wondered what happened to him!

Unpaid charity production

Keeping everything crossed as we really don't want to cancel

items.text:
Film crews are using Photoshop IDs and hand over cash envelopes to get paid?

Saturation's co-founders Jens Jacob & Simon Tam break down why film production financial tools haven't evolved like Figma, Frame.io, and Airtable did for their industries and how they're building the solution. From 20+ years in tech at Microsoft, Yahoo & Splunk to revolutionizing how $2B+ in budgets get managed for productions. Trusted by over 8,000 producers.

items.groupTitle: LA Actors, Agents, Casting Directors, Producers
items.summary:
Film crews are using Photoshop IDs and hand over cash envelopes to get paid?

Saturation's co-founders Jens Jacob & Simon Tam break down why film production financial tools haven't evolved like Figma, Frame.io, and Airtable did for their industries and how they're building the solution. From 20+ years in tech at Microsoft, Yahoo & Splunk to revolutionizing how $2B+ in budgets get managed for productions. Trusted by over 8,000 producers.

CASTING CALL - FEATURE FILM 

Please, do NOT email if you do not fit the brief!

Shooting Location: The Netherlands
Bruce male | 30 ‚Äì 45 | English: native 
Black, African American or Caribbean

Requirements:
Based in Europe (EU passport)
Native speaker of American English
Age range: 30‚Äì45 years old

European based American-English speaking actor for the role of BRUCE in the Dutch Comedy Film.

We are looking for an actor to play the role of young and ambitious American movie director Bruce in the upcoming Dutch comedy film.

The film is based on the best-selling novel Wen Er Maar Aan, written by Dutch actress and author Maike Meijer.

Shooting date: December 3th 2025 in the Netherlands 
Travel day: December 2th 2025 (Travel day back on the same day as the shooting day or the morning after)

Fee:
‚Ç¨4.000 all-in (shooting day + travel day(s))
Overnight stay will be covered by the production
Travel expenses will be covered by the production

If you are selected to record a self-tape, you will receive further details via email.

>> ancagency_submissions@hotmail.com

items.text:
**Casting for: East Asian actors, all types, all ages**

Holding open auditions for Asian actors, men and women, for a number of Asian film and episodic projects (action, thriller, drama, rom-com) we are working on.

East Asian ethnicity, looking for early 20's look (for group 1) and all ages (for group 2). Non-union. Payment status depends on the project.

Auditions are Friday, Saturday, Sunday, October 10th, 11th, 12th in East Vancouver studio. You will perform a short set of sides and then do a monologue of your choice.

Shooting will be throughout Fall and Winter 2025/2026.

If interested, please email castingproject604@gmail.comNOSPAM (remove 'NOSPAM') with your photos, resume with a cover letter about your experience or any training you have had and your availability for the three dates.

Shortlisted talent will be asked to audition.

Thank you for your attention.

items.text:
**Casting for: Korean Kpop Idol types, early 20's.**

Holding open auditions for several projects we are working on, looking for actors and actresses who can play  Korean Kpop singers and idols. This is not a music project, this is a short film/webseries project, thus looking for acting talent.

Asian ethnicity, early 20's look, attractive, in shape. You do not need to be Korean and you do not need to know how to sing (but if you can, that is a bonus). Non-union. Paid (TBD).

Auditions are Friday, Saturday, Sunday, October 10th, 11th, 12th in East Vancouver studio. You will perform a short set of sides and then do a monologue of your choice.

Shooting will be in Winter 2026.

If interested, please email castingproject604@gmail.comNOSPAM (remove 'NOSPAM') with your photos, resume with a cover letter about your experience or any training you have had and your availability for the three dates.

Shortlisted talent will be asked to audition.

Thank you for your attention.

Tickets are now available for our upcoming Actors and Filmmakers Networking Event, taking place on Sunday, October 26th.

 

Networking is essential for advancing your career in the industry, and Marble Academy has proudly facilitated these events for years. With over 90 attendees, our June gathering was a tremendous success, and we are determined to build on that momentum.

 

You will have the opportunity to connect with accomplished actors, visionary directors, prominent producers, and skilled crew members who can offer valuable insights and spark meaningful collaborations.

 

Think about it, if there were an event where you could connect with exceptionally talented cast and crew who could help bring your next project to life, wouldn‚Äôt you want to be there?

 

So, join us on Sunday, October 26th, from 2 PM to 6:30 PM at HOME Mcr, located at 2 Tony Wilson Place, Manchester, M15 4FN.

 

Secure your tickets through this link:

https://www.eventbrite.co.uk/e/actors-and-filmmakers-networking-event-tickets-1509159349239 

 

I look forward to seeing you there!

üåü Get Ready to Ignite Your Acting Passion with Our Exciting Workshop! üåü

 

Our last Self-Tape Workshop filled up quickly, leaving many interested individuals unable to attend, but don‚Äôt worry, we're excited to announce that another chance is just around the corner!

 

Join us at Marble Academy in Swinton, Manchester, on Monday, December 1st

 

You'll acquire practical insights and techniques that'll enhance your performance in auditions, boost your confidence on camera and create standout self-tapes!

 

**Spaces are VERY Limited!**

To claim your spot, email us at marbleacademy@hotmail.com with ‚ÄòSELF-TAPE WORKSHOP‚Äô in the subject line.

ùêèùê•ùêûùêöùê¨ùêû ùêûùêßùê¨ùêÆùê´ùêû ùê≠ùê°ùêöùê≠ ùê≤ùê®ùêÆùê´ ùê´ùêûùê¨ùêûùê´ùêØùêöùê≠ùê¢ùê®ùêß ùê¢ùê¨ ùê¨ùêÆùêõùê¶ùê¢ùê≠ùê≠ùêûùêù ùêõùê≤ ùêÖùê´ùê¢ùêùùêöùê≤, ùêçùê®ùêØùêûùê¶ùêõùêûùê´ ùüèùüíùê≠ùê°.

These materials will be accompanied by the workshop address and additional details, which will be sent to you via email.

 

We look forward to seeing you there.

The Brookside Theatre, Romford is urgently looking for a male actor (playing age 45-60) for their Halloween production; THE ADDAMS FAMILY 

Role: Mal Beineke (Actor with good comic timing. Does need to sing a few lines but these are character vocals)
Accent: US (General or NYC)

Sadly due to an injury and subsequent surgery, the actor playing role has had to withdraw

Rehearsals: Weekday evenings and Sunday daytimes (some flexibility)

Show dates: 29th Oct - 2nd Nov 2025

Venue: Brookside Theatre, Romford (2 mins walk from Elizabeth Line Station / Free Parking)

Unpaid charity production

If you think you can step in and save the show then please get in touch asap - email casting@brooksidetheatre.com or PM me

Keeping everything crossed as we really don't want to cancel

#castingcall #casting #addamsfamilymusical #musicaltheatre #stage #stageshow

items.text:
Heyyy! I‚Äôm Anne Musisi and I‚Äôm an actor, director, and career development coach with a mission to help creatives and actors thrive. Drawing on decades of experience in global theatre, screen, and coaching, I‚Äôve created a wellbeing tool designed specifically for actors and creatives. My mission is to help you overcome self-doubt, reconnect with your creative core, and build a sustainable, fulfilling career.

It is also a tool that can be used by therapists, coaches and facilitators to spark deeper conversations and even provide a thematic structure for your workshops. 

My work merges creative practice with personal growth and career strategy. This tool is the practical embodiment of my belief: that when creatives nurture their inner life, their art and profession flourish too.

If you or anyone are interested in learning more, do feel free to DM. I‚Äôd love to chat more.
https://www.annemusisi.com

Shooting Location: The Netherlands
Bruce male | 30 ‚Äì 45 | English: native 
Black, African American or Caribbean

Requirements:
Based in Europe (EU passport)
Native speaker of American English
Age range: 30‚Äì45 years old

European based American-English speaking actor for the role of BRUCE in the Dutch Comedy Film.

We are looking for an actor to play the role of young and ambitious American movie director Bruce in the upcoming Dutch comedy film.

The film is based on the best-selling novel Wen Er Maar Aan, written by Dutch actress and author Maike Meijer.

Shooting date: December 3th 2025 in the Netherlands 
Travel day: December 2th 2025 (Travel day back on the same day as the shooting day or the morning after)

Fee:
‚Ç¨4.000 all-in (shooting day + travel day(s))
Overnight stay will be covered by the production
Travel expenses will be covered by the production
